{{Lunisolar May}} '''May 4''' is the 4th day of the month {{ill|May (Lunisolar)|ja|5月 (旧暦)|lt=May|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 5th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Tomobiki|ja|友引|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Events == * {{ill|Gangyō|ja|元暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 2nd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[878]] {{ill|June 9|ja|6月9日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Fujiwara Hosanori|ja|藤原保則|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} departed for the pacification of Mutsu in Ezo.<ref>{{Cite web|title=【要出典】|url=|accessdate=2021-02}}</ref> * {{ill|Genki (era)|ja|元亨|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 3rd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1572]] {{ill|June 14|ja|6月14日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Shimazu Yoshihiro|ja|島津義弘|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} defeated 3,000 soldiers of the 【Itō army|伊東軍】 with only 300 men at Shinmakai-in during the 【Battle of Kizakihara|木崎原の戦い】. * {{ill|Keichō|ja|慶長|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1597]] {{ill|June 18|ja|6月18日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The Tenshu of Fushimi Castle was completed; subsequently, {{ill|Toyotomi Hideyoshi|ja|豊臣秀吉|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} and his son Hideyori relocated there. == Births == * <“[[Otomo Yoshinobu]]” has a note stating “January 3”.> * {{ill|Kyōhō|ja|享保|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 8th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1723]] {{ill|June 6|ja|6月6日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Ike Taiga|ja|池大雅|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a painter from the Nan domain (died [[1776]]). * {{ill|Tenpō|ja|天保|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 14th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1843]] {{ill|June 1|ja|6月1日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Saigō Jūdō|ja|西郷従道|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a military figure and the younger brother of Saigō Takamori (died [[1902]]). == Deaths == * {{ill|Tenbun|ja|文永|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 19th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1550]] {{ill|May 20|ja|5月20日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Ashikaga Yoshiharu|ja|足利義晴|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 12th Shōgun of the Ashikaga Shogunate (born [[1511]]). == Commemorations == * 【Yukkanihee】 (沖縄県) – In various regions, the “Haarī” is performed. Historically, children were gifted toys to wish for their growth. “Yukkanihee” means “the day of the fourth” in the lunisolar calendar.<ref>{{Cite web|title=旧暦行事カレンダー Lunisolar April～6月|url=http://www.okinawastory.jp/contents/kurashi/calendar4_6|publisher=沖縄観光情報WEBサイト おきなわ物語|accessdate=2018-06-24}}</ref> * 【Naha Haarī】 * 【Itoman Haarī】
