== Events == * {{ill|Gangyō|ja|元暦|qq=}} 2nd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=}} [[878]] {{ill|June 9|ja|6月9日|qq=}}) – {{ill|Fujiwara Hosanori|ja|藤原保則|qq=}} departed for the pacification of Mutsu in Ezo.<ref>{{Cite web|title=【要出典】|url=|accessdate=2021-02|qq=}}</ref> * {{ill|Genki (era)|ja|元亨|qq=}} 3rd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=}} [[1572]] {{ill|June 14|ja|6月14日|qq=}}) – {{ill|Shimazu Yoshihiro|ja|島津義弘|qq=}} defeated 3,000 soldiers of the 【Itō army|伊東軍】 with only 300 men at Shinmakai-in during the 【Battle of Kizakihara|木崎原の戦い】. * {{ill|Keichō|ja|慶長|qq=}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=}} [[1597]] {{ill|June 18|ja|6月18日|qq=}}) – The Tenshu of Fushimi Castle was completed; subsequently, {{ill|Toyotomi Hideyoshi|ja|豊臣秀吉|qq=}} and his son Hideyori relocated there. == Births == * <“[[Otomo Yoshinobu]]” has a note stating “January 3”.> * {{ill|Kyōhō|ja|享保|qq=}} 8th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=}} [[1723]] {{ill|June 6|ja|6月6日|qq=}}) – {{ill|Ike Taiga|ja|池大雅|qq=}}, a painter from the Nan domain (died [[1776]]). * {{ill|Tenpō|ja|天保|qq=}} 14th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=}} [[1843]] {{ill|June 1|ja|6月1日|qq=}}) – {{ill|Saigō Jūdō|ja|西郷従道|qq=}}, a military figure and the younger brother of Saigō Takamori (died [[1902]]). == Deaths == * {{ill|Tenbun|ja|文永|qq=}} 19th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=}} [[1550]] {{ill|May 20|ja|5月20日|qq=}}) – {{ill|Ashikaga Yoshiharu|ja|足利義晴|qq=}}, the 12th Shōgun of the Ashikaga Shogunate (born [[1511]]). == Commemorations == * 【Yukkanihee】 (沖縄県) – In various regions, the “Haarī” is performed. Historically, children were gifted toys to wish for their growth. “Yukkanihee” means “the day of the fourth” in the lunisolar calendar.<ref>{{Cite web|title=旧暦行事カレンダー Lunisolar April～6月|url=http://www.okinawastory.jp/contents/kurashi/calendar4_6|publisher=沖縄観光情報WEBサイト おきなわ物語|accessdate=2018-06-24|qq=}}</ref> * 【Naha Haarī】 * 【Itoman Haarī】
