== Events == * [[:en:Genryaku|Gangyō]] 2nd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[878]] [[:en:June 9|June 9]]) – [[:en:Fujiwara no Yasunori|Fujiwara Hosanori]] departed for the pacification of Mutsu in Ezo.<ref>{{Cite web|title=【Citation needed】|url=|accessdate=2021-02|qq=}}</ref> * [[:en:Genkō (1321–1324)|Genki (era)]] 3rd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1572]] [[:en:June 14|June 14]]) – [[:en:Shimazu Yoshihiro|Shimazu Yoshihiro]] defeated 3,000 soldiers of the 【Itō army|伊東軍】 with only 300 men at Shinmakai-in during the 【Battle of Kizakihara|木崎原の戦い】. * [[:en:Keichō|Keichō]] 2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1597]] [[:en:June 18|June 18]]) – The Tenshu of Fushimi Castle was completed; subsequently, [[:en:Toyotomi Hideyoshi|Toyotomi Hideyoshi]] and his son Hideyori relocated there. == Births == * <“[[Otomo Yoshinobu]]” has a note stating “January 3”.> * [[:en:Kyōhō|Kyōhō]] 8th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1723]] [[:en:June 6|June 6]]) – [[:en:Ike no Taiga|Ike Taiga]], a painter from the Nan domain (died [[1776]]). * [[:en:Tenpō|Tenpō]] 14th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1843]] [[:en:June 1|June 1]]) – [[:en:Saigō Jūdō|Saigō Jūdō]], a military figure and the younger brother of Saigō Takamori (died [[1902]]). == Deaths == * [[:en:Bun'ei|Tenbun]] 19th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1550]] [[:en:May 20|May 20]]) – [[:en:Ashikaga Yoshiharu|Ashikaga Yoshiharu]], the 12th Shōgun of the Ashikaga Shogunate (born [[1511]]). == Commemorations == * 【Yukkanihee】 (沖縄県) – In various regions, the “Haarī” is performed. Historically, children were gifted toys to wish for their growth. “Yukkanihee” means “the day of the fourth” in the lunisolar calendar.<ref>{{Cite web|title=旧暦行事カレンダー Lunisolar April～6月|url=http://www.okinawastory.jp/contents/kurashi/calendar4_6|publisher=沖縄観光情報WEBサイト おきなわ物語|accessdate=2018-06-24|qq=}}</ref> * 【Naha Haarī】 * 【Itoman Haarī】
